snippet.textDisplay: I get it, in these vlogs they are scripted and also they just having fun filming. I see their content as being better suited for more mature audiences (teenagers), but, I know that their main audience are kids. Dobriks content can be really innapropriate (over sexualized, mature subject matter and bad language among other things) for younger audiences, and im no bible thumper, but is it really alright that this is shown to our youth who are very impressionable. If you watch a bunch of his videos in a neutral unbiased manner you will see what I am saying. Youtube censors content that is nowhere near as inappropriate ie. historical and current event videos, but they dont censor content like this that parents would universally have agreed is not very appropriate for kids. I dont even think his content is age restricted. Im not even a parent im a college student and I see this.
